				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\upmu \hbox {m}}$$\end{document} filter. While DOC only refers to the mass of the carbon within the dissolved organic molecules, the term dissolved organic matter (DOM) refers to the bulk of organic molecules, including other atoms such as nitrogen, oxygen, sulfur and hydrogen. Figure 2 shows various size fractions belonging to DOM. The amount of DOC in shallow groundwater systems usually ranges from 0.2 to 15mgCL-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
