The water composition differs from the margin regions of the basin to the center of the basin as percolating meteoric water from the MB borders (Swabian and Franconian Albs, and the Bohemian Massif) recharges the groundwater (Andrews et al. 1987; Goldbrunner 2000; Stichler et al. 1987). Hence, the age of the fluids is reported to be between 10,000 and 50,000 years (Andrews et al. 1987; Goldbrunner 1997). Generally, the concentration of total dissolved solids does not exceed 1gL-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
